> Whats the difference in the spindles from pre - '63 to the ones from '63-'67 
> ?
> 
Hi Collie,
Basicly the 1955-63 spindles and trailing arms use small diameter link pins 
made for 1,500Lbs. payload.  The 1964-67 use a bigger diameter link pins for 
2,000Lbs. payload.
Eric&Barb
